5|$|Modern {{evaluation}} <b>of</b> <b>the</b> <b>book</b> <b>is</b> from {{a variety}} of perspectives, including the history of Darwinism, the history of the Thayer debate on the purpose of camouflage, the mechanisms of camouflage, sexual selection, and mimicry. Beddard is seen as having covered a wide swath of modern biology with both theory and experiment.|$|E
